<FIRST>r f PM-TischInvests 1stLd-Writethru f0018 12-27 0208</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Tisch Invests, 1st Ld-Writethru, f0018,0213</SECOND>
<HEAD>CBS Executive Tisch Buys Bank of Boston Stock</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Restores dropped word `million' in 3rd graf.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An investment group including CBS chairman and
chief executive Lawrence A. Tisch has purchased 6.6 percent of the
Bank of Boston Corp., filings with the Securities and Exchange
Commission show.
   Tisch and his partners bought the stock for investment purposes
and have no intention of seeking control of the bank, according to
the filings Tuesday.
   The $94.5 million investment was made by Tisch, other members of
his family and FLF Associates, a New York-based firm that
represents four of Tisch's sons.
   The group said it holds 4.7 million common shares in the bank,
and plans to review its investment from time to time. The group
said it might increase or decrease its holdings, depending on
market and other conditions.
   Tisch is also chairman of Loews Corp., which owns CNA Financial
Insurance, Lorrilard Tobacco, and 25 percent of CBS.
   Bank of Boston's stock has declined steadily and is in its
lowest price range since 1985. The bank recently announced a $125
million third quarter loss due to problems with real estate
construction loans.
   Bank of Boston stock closed up 1] at 18[ Tuesday.
</TEXT>
