<DOCNO> AP891227-0175 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-12-27-89 1031EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>u f PM-WallStreet10am     12-27 0221</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 10am,0236</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market was little changed today,
continuing the trendless pattern that prevailed on Tuesday.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials slipped .22 to 2,709.04
in the first half hour of trading.
   Gainers outnumbered losers by about 6 to 5 in nationwide trading
of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 452 up, 376 down and
557 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 14.90 million shares as of 10
a.m. on Wall Street.
   Analysts found little in the economic news to stir the market
out of its recent lethargy. Interest rates were narrowly mixed in
the credit markets.
   Traders also appeared to be unsettled by doubts that a
significant yearend rally was in the making.
   Hilton Hotels fell 5{ to 84\ on a report that efforts to sell
the company had attracted lower bids than had been predicted.
