distributions totaling $1.38 a share to holders of record Friday.
   Gainers among the blue chips included Philip Morris, up \ at
40\; Sears Roebuck, up { at 37~; International Business Machines,
up \ at 94}; Ford Motor, up \ at 43\, and General Electric, up ] at
63}.
   Hilton Hotels fell 6~ to 82~ on a report that efforts to sell
the company had attracted lower bids than had been predicted.
   Rexene Corp. tumbled 1~ to 4\. The company, whose stock traded
as high as 22] earlier this year, suspended its dividend, citing a
variety of reasons.
   As measured by Wilshire Associates' index of more than 5,000
actively traded stocks, the market increased $17.79 billion, or
0.53 percent, in value.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks
gained .97 to 192.69.
   Standard &amp; Poor's industrial index rose 2.51 to 398.16, and
S&amp;P's 500-stock composite index was up 2.00 at 348.81.
   The NASDAQ composite index for the over-the-counter market added
3.55 to 448.81. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index closed at 372.96, up 2.16.
