<FIRST>r f BC-ThomsonNewspapers     12-27 0195</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Thomson Newspapers,0205</SECOND>
<HEAD>Thomson Newspapers Announces Management Changes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TORONTO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thomson Newspapers Corp. announced Wednesday a
series of management changes effective Jan. 1.
   Kerry Lambie, 50, becomes executive vice president for
operations, assuming responsiblity for newspaper operations in
Canada and the United States. He will remain in Toronto.
   Frank Miles, 64, becomes executive vice president for
acquisitions, which includes effecting and integrating
acquisitions. He remains in Chicago.
   Lambie and Miles will report to Michael Johnston, president and
chief operating officer of Thomson Newspapers Corp., a subsidiary
of Thomson Corp. of Toronto
   Michael Sheppard, 40, replaces Lambie as senior vice president
and general manager for Canada. He will move to Toronto from
Chicago.
   D.P. Hicks, 55, replaces Miles as senior vice president and
general manager for the United States.
   In other appointments, Allan Weir, 47, joins the company as
director of human resources. R.J. Hogg, 55, moves to director of
marketing from circulation director and Charles Wilson, 41,
previously manager of administration, becomes director of
administration.
   Thomson Newspapers publishes 41 daily and 19 non-daily
newspapers in Canada, 117 daily and 25 non-daily newspapers in the
United States, and several special-subject publications in both
countries.
</TEXT>
