<FIRST>r f BC-Obit-Hooten     12-27 0115</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Obit-Hooten,0123</SECOND>
<HEAD>Hearst Corp. Broadcasting Executive Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mickey L. Hooten, a broadcasting executive for
Hearst Corp., has died of a heart attack at age 54.
   Hooten, who died Sunday, joined Hearst in 1974 as program
manager of WTAE-TV in Pittsburgh.
   In 1976, he became vice president and general manager of
Hearst's WISN-TV in Milwaukee.
   He was named general manager of television for Hearst
Broadcasting in 1984 and became a corporate vice president in 1986.
   Hooten also worked at KTBS-TV in Shreveport, La., WTOL-TV in
Toledo, Ohio, WIS-TV in Columbia, S.C., and WGHP-TV in High Point,
N.C.
   He was a past chairman of the ABC Television Network Affiliates
Board of Governors.
</TEXT>
